      "side": 1,
      "message": "Overwriting the value of `t-\u003evrrp.n_addrs` will change what gets printed in the line of trace output that displays the contents of the fixed fields so it will not reflect what was received in the packet. I think it could be confusing to a user if they know advertisements are being sent by a peer with some number of virtual IP addresses but the trace output says the received packet had less than that.\n\nInstead of modifying the value of `t-\u003evrrp.n_addrs` here, there should be a separate field `u8 n_addrs` added to vrrp_trace_t to indicate the number of addresses populated in the addrs field and that new field should be set here.\n\nThen format_vrrp_trace() can look at both t-\u003evrrp.n_addrs and t-\u003en_addrs (e.g. `for (i \u003d 0; i \u003c t-\u003evrrp.n_addrs \u0026\u0026 i \u003c t-\u003en_addrs; i++) { ... }`when deciding how many addresses to format.",
